[2026-03-14T20:06:02Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FXHswbxjWP3Y1Go3ySfEeD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document of my findings.\n\n## Summary of Workflow Graph Rendering in Cloche Web UI\n\nI've thoroughly explored the codebase to understand how workflow graphs are rendered. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. Web UI Files and Architecture\n\n**Template Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Master layout template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Main workflow graph visualization (lines 1-577)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Individual run details and step execution tracking\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Run listing page\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Project listing page\n\n**Static Assets:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Styling including DAG visualization styles (lines 477-516)\n\n**Go HTTP Handler:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main handler serving the web dashboard\n\n### 2. Workflow Graph Visualization Implementation\n\n**Location in Code:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 100-434)\n\nThe workflow graph is rendered entirely on the **client-side using SVG** with a JavaScript algorithm:\n\n**Data Flow:**\n1. API endpoint `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` (handler line 167) returns JSON with workflow definitions\n2. JavaScript function `loadWorkflows()` (line 103) fetches the data\n3. Function `showWorkflow()` (line 172) performs layout and renders SVG\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n| Function | Lines | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `loadWorkflows()` | 103-132 | Fetches workflows from API, separates by location (container/host) |\n| `switchLocation()` | 134-141 | Toggles between container and host workflow views |\n| `renderWorkflowTabs()` | 143-163 | Creates tabs for multiple workflows in same location |\n| `showFilteredWorkflow()` | 165-170 | Selects which workflow to display |\n| `showWorkflow()` | 172-434 | **Main layout and SVG rendering algorithm** |\n\n### 3. Workflow Graph Layout Algorithm\n\n**Algorithm: Sugiyama-style Hierarchical Layout** (Lines 201-305)\n\nThe layout process:\n\n1. **Build Adjacency Maps** (lines 191-199)\n   - Forward adjacency: `from → [wires]`\n   - Reverse adjacency: `to → [from]` (unique predecessors)\n\n2. **Topological Sort** (lines 204-226)\n   - Kahn's algorithm to order steps\n   - Handles cycles by adding remaining unvisited steps\n\n3. **Layer Assignment** (lines 228-244)\n   - Assigns each step to a layer based on longest path from source\n   - Formula: `layerOf[n] = max(layerOf[parent]) + 1`\n   - Terminals (`done`, `abort`) placed in rightmost layer\n\n4. **Barycenter Reordering** (lines 252-282)\n   - 4 passes (2 forward, 2 backward) to minimize edge crossings\n   - Forward pass: Orders nodes by average parent position\n   - Backward pass: Orders nodes by average child position\n\n5. **Position Calculation** (lines 284-305)\n   - Nodes centered within their layer\n   - Constants:\n     - `nodeW = 180` pixels (width)\n     - `nodeH = 48` pixels (height)\n     - `layerGap = 80` pixels (vertical spacing)\n     - `nodeGap = 40` pixels (horizontal spacing)\n     - `nonsuccOffset = 35` pixels (horizontal offset for non-success paths)\n\n### 4. Data Structures for Workflows\n\n**From Domain Layer:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string                  // Workflow name\n    Location  WorkflowLocation        // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step        // Step definitions by name\n    Wiring    []Wire                  // Edge definitions\n    Collects  []Collect               // Merge patterns for multiple inputs\n    EntryStep string                  // Starting step\n    Config    map[string]string       // Workflow-level configuration\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string            // Step identifier\n    Type    StepType          // \"agent\", \"script\", or \"workflow\"\n    Results []string          // Possible outcomes (e.g., \"success\", \"failed\")\n    Config  map[string]string // Step-specific configuration\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string           // Source step name\n    Result    string           // Result path (e.g., \"success\", \"failed\")\n    To        string           // Target step name (or \"done\"/\"abort\")\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping  // Environment variable mappings\n}\n\ntype Collect struct {\n    Mode       CollectMode        // \"all\" or \"any\"\n    Conditions []WireCondition    // Multiple input conditions\n    To         string             // Merge target\n}\n```\n\n**API Response Types:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1473-1490)\n\n```go\ntype apiWire struct {\n    From   string `json:\"from\"`\n    Result string `json:\"result\"`\n    To     string `json:\"to\"`\n}\n\ntype apiStepDef struct {\n    Name    string            `json:\"name\"`\n    Type    string            `json:\"type\"`\n    Results []string          `json:\"results\"`\n    Config  map[string]string `json:\"config\"`\n}\n\ntype apiWorkflow struct {\n    Name      string       `json:\"name\"`\n    File      string       `json:\"file\"`\n    Location  string       `json:\"location\"`\n    Steps     []apiStepDef `json:\"steps\"`\n    Wires     []apiWire    `json:\"wires\"`\n    EntryStep string       `json:\"entry_step\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Workflow DSL Path Definitions\n\n**From `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`:**\n\nResults are represented as strings that flow through the workflow:\n- **Success paths:** `\"success\"`, `\"ok\"`, `\"done\"`, `\"pass\"` (recognized by the function `isSuccessResult()` at line 328)\n- **Failure paths:** Any other result name (typically `\"failed\"`, `\"fail\"`, `\"error\"`)\n- **Terminal nodes:** `\"done\"` and `\"abort\"` (built-in terminals)\n\n**Path Resolution:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` (lines 62-115)\n\n```go\ntype OutputPath struct {\n    Segments []PathSegment  // JSON path navigation\n}\n\ntype PathSegment struct {\n    Kind  SegmentKind  // SegmentField or SegmentIndex\n    Field string       // For field access (e.g., \".result\")\n    Index int          // For array indexing (e.g., \"[0]\")\n}\n\n// Evaluate navigates JSON output using path segments\n// Examples: No segments returns raw output, \".field.subfield\" navigates JSON\n```\n\n### 6. Graph Rendering Details\n\n**SVG Generation** (lines 310-433):\n\n**Node Rendering:**\n- Regular steps: Rectangle with icon (emoji) + name\n- Terminal nodes: Rounded rectangles (\"done\" = green, \"abort\" = red)\n- Click handler opens drawer with step details\n\n**Edge Rendering:**\n- Bezier curves (quadratic) connecting nodes top-to-bottom\n- Success paths: Normal stroke (muted color)\n- Non-success paths: Offset 35px right, different color (red tint), dashed marker\n\n**Merge Pattern for Multiple Inputs:**\n- Multiple sources → merge at horizontal line → single terminal\n- Each source curves to merge line with offset\n- Merge line has dots at connection points\n- Single line from merge to terminal\n\n**CSS Classes for Styling** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`):\n- `.dag-svg` - SVG container\n- `.dag-node` - Step nodes (clickable)\n- `.dag-node-rect` - Rectangle shape\n- `.dag-node-text` - Node label text\n- `.dag-edge` - Regular edge\n- `.dag-edge-nonsuccess` - Failed path (offset, red color)\n- `.dag-edge-label` - Result name on edge\n- `.dag-merge-line` - Horizontal merge collector\n- `.dag-merge-dot` - Connection points on merge line\n- `.dag-terminal-done` - Green terminal\n- `.dag-terminal-abort` - Red terminal\n\n### 7. Step Drawer Implementation\n\n**Location:** `project_detail.html` (lines 42-49, 436-469)\n\n- Side panel that slides in from right\n- Shows step details: type, results, configuration\n- Fetches step content via `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n- Closes on Escape key or close button\n\n### 8. Key Implementation Files Summary\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Components |\n|------|---------|-----------------|\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | HTTP handlers | `handleAPIWorkflows()`, API data structures |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` | Graph rendering | SVG generation, layout algorithm, interactivity |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` | Step execution | Step table, live log streaming, accordion UI |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` | Styling | DAG visualization CSS, badge colors, responsive layout |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | Domain logic | Step, Wire, Workflow, OutputPath data structures |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` | DSL parsing | Parses .cloche files into domain structures |\n\nThis architecture provides a clean separation: the backend parses workflows and serves structured JSON, while the frontend handles all layout and visualization logic with client-side rendering."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7fa5c1b9e1d8fcfc (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57267\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 67106</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c8efca8-0543-449d-b96b-ca9c239a2f48","uuid":"a40382c6-46e7-4ab3-a75f-f3ee39d38f7c","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand how workflow graphs are rendered in the web UI. I need to find:\n\n1. The web UI files (HTML, JS, CSS, Go templates) that render workflow graphs\n2. How workflow steps/nodes are currently laid out and connected\n3. How the workflow DSL defines paths (succeeded, failed, etc.)\n4