20-cloche-system-design.md-191-2. Copies project files into the container at `/workspace`\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md-192-3. Starts the container with `cloche-agent` as entrypoint, passing the workflow name\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md:193:4. `cloche-agent` parses the workflow, walks the graph, executes steps\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md-194-5. Agent streams status events to `cloched` via stdout\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md-195-6. At step boundaries, modified files are pushed to the host via git (agent-specific branch)\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md-196-7. On completion (`done`/`abort`), container is stopped\n--\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md-165-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md-166-### Engine Rewrite\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md-167-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md:168:The engine changes from a linear loop to a concurrent DAG walker.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md-169-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md-170-**State:**\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-design.md-171-\n--\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-16-1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-17-2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-18-3. **Tasks** — live task pipeline view showing discovered tasks, their status, and assigned runs\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:19:4. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-20-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-21-## Route\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-22-\n--\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-142-- Two-level tab navigation:\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-143-  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-144-  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:145:- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-146-  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-147-  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-148-  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n--\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-154-  - For script steps: the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-155-  - For host script steps: contents of a referenced script file under `.cloche/scripts/` (text files only); the content panel is hidden when no displayable content is available\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-156-  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:157:  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-158-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:159:### DAG rendering\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-160-Client-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-161-layers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-162-heuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-163-top-to-bottom with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-164-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:165:Non-success wires (any result not in `success`, `ok`, `done`, `pass`) are offset\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-166-horizontally from the main flow so they don't overlap the happy-path edges. These wires\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:167:use a distinct failure color and reduced opacity (`dag-edge-nonsuccess` class) with a\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-168-matching arrowhead marker.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-169-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-170-When multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-171-collector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a horizontal dashed line,\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-172-which feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. Non-success wires within a merge bus\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:173:are offset to their own horizontal positions, and the collector line extends to cover them.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-174-This reduces wire clutter as graphs grow in complexity.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-175-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:176:The DAG container scrolls vertically when the graph exceeds the panel height.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-177-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-178-### API additions\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-179-\n--\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-869-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-870----\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-871-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md:872:### Task 8: Rewrite engine as DAG walker\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-873-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-874-**Files:**\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-875-- Modify: `internal/engine/engine.go`\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-876-- Modify: `internal/engine/engine_test.go`\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-877-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md:878:This is the largest task. The engine changes from a single-step loop to a concurrent DAG walker.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-879-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-880-**Step 1: Write failing tests for fanout and collect**\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-881-\n--\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-1037-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-1038-**Step 3: Rewrite engine**\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-1039-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md:1040:Replace the `Run` method in `engine.go` with the DAG walker. Key changes:\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-1041-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-1042-1. Track `active` step count, `completed` map, and `pending` collect states.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-1043-2. Use a results channel for step completion notifications.\n--\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-1062-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edg