orkspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-170-When multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-171-collector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a horizontal dashed line,\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-172-which feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. Non-success wires within a merge bus\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:173:are offset to their own horizontal positions, and the collector line extends to cover them.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-174-This reduces wire clutter as graphs grow in complexity.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-175-\ndocs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md:176:The DAG container scrolls vertically when the graph exceeds the panel height.\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-177-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-178-### API additions\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md-179-\n--\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-869-\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-870----\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-871-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md:872:### Task 8: Rewrite engine as DAG walker\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-873-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-874-**Files:**\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-875-- Modify: `internal/engine/engine.go`\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-876-- Modify: `internal/engine/engine_test.go`\n/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md-877-\ndocs/plans/2026-02-20-edge-selection-implementation.md:878:This is the largest task. The engine changes from a single-step loop to a concurrent DAG walker.\n/workspace/